									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 345 times<br>
									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_4.gif' border=0 alt='4 ratings - 4.0 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Arbosch</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>That warriors will be better at pure tanking than ANY other class (including Knights) should not be questioned. It is what warriors are. It is all they are. It is all they have been. Warriors will always have a higher AC cap (both soft and hard) and AC potential. Warriors will always have the highest HP potential. They always have.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Warriors are the tank of choice when the content in question is well over the equipment range of knights. Do knights tank raid targets? Yes, they do. Do they take the damage as well as defensive warriors can? Not even close. But anything a nondefensive warrior can tank is potentially tankable by knights. So why do knights MT some raid targets? Because of crazy things like memory blur or death traps, that require fast aggro that a warrrior cannot even begin to compete with.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As far as the single group concerns go, arbosch, we have already seen SOEs answer to this one. How long has it been since a warrrior ability has experienced a direct nerf? But we endure this one in the name of balance. Sure, a warrior who is undergeared could potentially take on a trial boss and win under defensive. But the group he is with has got to be above par on every other category to even think this warrior can tank the mobs gettting to the boss.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Don't piss on your potential as a player, arbosch. Knights are VERY strong in all areas they are designed to be a part of. As far as rangers tanking better than knights, even for a 30 second encounter, I doubt this is a major issue once knights finally get an avoidance disc. Knights will always win out over rangers as group tanks due to higher AC and higher HP.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What do knights need to be able to tank better?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1) Avoidance discs for those emergency moments</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2) Paladins need a way to use stuns even on stun immune mobs, for effect. Limit its abuse somehow, to avoid stun lock.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3) Shadowknights need a way to mitigate or avoid damage comparable to the same level that paladins use stuns. Some neat ideas on this, such as a percentage reverse damage shield or an accuracy debuff.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I will have to digress from Frodlin on this, though. Further rebalancing at this point is not warranted since OoW is two days away from release. GoD was supposed to be challenging to the top 10% of players, to slow them down from chewing through this content as fast as they have done with almost every single expansion to date. I think GoD has been responsible for many players finally deciding to end their EQ career, both because its level of asinine difiiculty (time sink issues, raiding requirements, etc) and because of how it limits even casual players from further advancement into this expansion. I mean, if the stepping-off requirement to get beyond Natimbi is to be PoP Elemental geared (or VT geared even) goes flat into the face of SOEs promise to make no expansion require the presence of previous expansions. GoD offers next to nothing for the casual player, and was designed to frustrate even the highest guild players. Who knows, maybe OoW will fix the problems we have all experienced with GoD.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Personally, the only thing holding me to this game at this point is the friends I still have left playing. And even they are talking about leaving EQ once WoW or EQ2 goes gold. And a large nunmber of those are already burnt on SOE products (can anyone say SWG?) so I think Blizzard is going to see the influx of a lot of EQ refugees.</DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
