			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
If the named mobs in KodTaz/Yxxta were toned down a little bit, one of the Malevolant priests in Ikkinz 2 trial&nbsp;were made fully slowable, then things would be just about perfect.<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>I've got NO idea why you so fervently hold on to that. I don't want to be mean or anything...but i just don't understand it. And later you go on to say something a lot better about making defensive not a necessity. In my opinion, GoD problems start in Sewer 1. The rest are gimp yes. The unslowable mobs and the stonemite can absolutely rape knights.</P>
<P>I've done quite well for my gear level I suppose, I would of got through tanking Vxed if not for expedition deciding to crash on us. Even then I must of died 5-6 times.</P>
<P>Oddly enough, something I think would help Knights a lot at the moment would be being able to use Anger 3. It can be tough to hold aggro when&nbsp;you need to patch yourself a lot (even with 2 healers!). It's more than likely a combination of things that have gotten us knights so upset, the gradual decrease of our aggro prowess, our loss of stun mitigation due to so many immune mobs and of course the fact that we have no kind of disc. I think it's obvious a parry disc or whatever is essential for the Knight classes. A great example of this was when my guild was raiding fire the other night. We wiped to this mob we really shouldn't have (I guess we were slacking) and our raid leader says in /rsay Tanks, you need to call aggro when you pick it up (we were losing tanks quite fast). Another Pally says, well, i was just about to, but I died!. And i proceeded to add that actually knights need to call "I am tanking %t" before they even get aggro.</P>
<P>Another example I posted before was on Corinav, the raid&nbsp;can get very spread out at times on that raid. And me pulling one of the named off the casters with no void disc is insta death, which is just unrealistic when I'm supposedly *the* second choice tank after a Warrior. And of course, for single group content, when you pull the named who one rounds for 4k or whatever and the Shaman says "Dirty GoD mob has RESISTED slow!!", us Knights are gonna need that ripo disc. Not to mention a mob like that will stun us to holy hell, so maybe we wont even get&nbsp;a stun off and before it kills us, it'll ping pong off the shammy and cleric and kill them first.</P>
<P>Anyway, I'm rambling. But yeah, knights have it very tough atm, and it REALLY isn't restricted to a couple named mobs.<BR></P>
