			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Trilo, </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm gonna kind of go through your post point by point but in a wierd order cause my brain isnt' working well at the moment, so bear with me.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Just as an FYI:&nbsp; Ykesha augs are better than Anger 3 augs.&nbsp;&nbsp; Why warriors waste their AP's on Anger 3 instead of Ykesha will forever boggle my mind.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Anyhow, with Coirnav, I'm not real concerned about your tanking of rootable mobs, Paladins have been tanking those 3 nameds in Coir script forever, I've never even heard of warriors offtanking em, maybe tankign them after they depop and repop, but&nbsp;the aggro difference even today is *extreme* in that particular encounter.&nbsp;&nbsp; The fact that you CAN pull aggro off the casters makes you better at that job than me, there's no way in hell I can do it in time to be beneficial.&nbsp; My job in the Coir script&nbsp;was so funny... I'd sit around and hope I'm lucky enough to see a stray baby mob come by so I can kill it while I watch the AE squad get me lots and lots of yellow messages.&nbsp;&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Insofar as Gates issues starting at Stonemites, I totally disagree.&nbsp;&nbsp; While it's indeed possible for an undergeared warrior to do better against the nameds/stonemites if he's using a disc, he will be DEVASTATED by the trash mobs, I've seen this time and time again, the guy with the big head and /disc defensive thinks that he's invulnerable never makes it TO the stonemites to use it.&nbsp;&nbsp; I've also seen 8khp knights successfully tank them with little issue.&nbsp;&nbsp; Sewer 1 is a "gatekeeper" expedition, just like Tipt is.&nbsp; They're designed to make certain that you're of a given gear/skill level to allow you to move forward without being a danger to yourelf or others around you.&nbsp; Both of them have that "failsafe" function of fairly tough routine mobs which prevent things like undergeared warriors and rangers from tanking through them.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
