			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>Rather than a thread where Paladins start with something we want/need, I'm curious on what the Warriors that frequent our boards think that Paladins need in order to achieve our goal of three balanced tank classes (and what they think our role should be).&nbsp; 
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Well I think OoW is going to address many paladin concerns if not directly , indirectly. The shield block AA for instance could bring a signifigant amount of mitigation. I would like to wait till around 3-4 weeks after OoW is out before I tried to answer this question. This way I can kinda see how the new levels, AAs, and gear will effect knights in both GoD , and OoW.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My current belief is that a void/riposte disc is not the best solution for knights. I posted earlier about how defensive gives the average warrior a chance to take on challenging content.&nbsp; A void disc lasts 12-24 seconds. I believe it would help balance out the higher end of the game ,but isnt going to make much of a difference to the average knight . The average knight imo needs some way to mitigate better, and for a considerable amount of time not just a few seconds.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The shield block AA might add this mitigation that is very much needed, and we will just have to wait and see how useful it is.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The highend paladin gets the benefit of archtype armors wich im my opinion favors them. Giving them very close to same ac/hp. While the average paladin gets class based armor like ornate. The buyable ldon archtype armor is somewhat a unbalancer if it has been auged out.&nbsp; I do believe for the most part though that the average paladin has a considerably larger gap between hp/ac ratio to the warriors. Now if they have auged out ldon they may well exceed there casual warrior brethren. Basically the gap IS the same but instead of the casual warrior being at 12k with a 1-1.5k gap , its more like the casual warrior is at 9k buffed , and the paladin is at 7500 - 7800 buffed. Now the gap is about the same at the highend , but ratio wise is greater.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Hopefully some of this will make sense as to where I stand on the issue. I think most of my concerns could easily be addressed in OoW and am patiently waiting on it to come out/</DIV>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 100; overflow: hidden;">
														<p>Katur Carus
Proud leader of
Final Evolution
