						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Hi Frodin <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;Yeah, I'm actually talking about the repopped version of the named on Corinav. I think lasted 2 seconds max on that mob. Prolly even a 6 second void would have saved me and possibly the raid (woohoo, we downed that squidy now).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The thing with sewer 1 is, if you do it right, you can actually forgo all the hard mobs bar 1 or 2. You can invis past everything once you've swam down the hole. Infact you've probably got time for two uses of /defensive during the trial as well I would of thought.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Worse case scenario, I think adding an aggro modifier two one our stun spells where it can aggro over say, a malo and 2 slow attempts or maybe 2-3 SLs would be very handy.</DIV>
<DIV>I'd say give it a 2 min recast tho. Combined with&nbsp;a void disc of course, that would make us the supreme offtank (for like, 18 seconds!). Otherwise it's often gonna be a case for Paladins that you're either group healing and just attacking or even in some case, I just sit on my horse and try keep people alive and feeling like a poor cleric. I don't think that prices Warriors out of the offtanking game either. On unmezzable mobs that need&nbsp;a long offtanking Pallies (or SKs) could buddy up with Warriors by locking down mobs then have Warriors transfer em over with taunt.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>18 seconds of parry every 15-30 mins I feel certainly isn't going to gimp Warriors and would make us Pallies feel a lot better.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Something I'd be happy to see in the case of Warriors is their non tanking DPS hugely increased. It doesn't sit well with me that the master of War does such pony DPS compared to other classes. I mean, when you're not tanking, everyone is backstabbing really.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It's a difficult arguement i guess, I mean, were Pallies ever meant to be tanks in the EQ sense? The way the game is now, with things like summon and whatever is that group dynamic tends to be tank, healer, slower, or even tank, healer, healer, slower and add DPS onto both of those. And that in general is the way groups are formed (aside the new, charmer, charmer, healer, snare, oh crap! tank groups). Paladins forte as the game stands, altho we moan about it,&nbsp;is tanking. We only work as very short term healers (we eat mana like it's going out of fashion), we don't slow and we don't do DPS. We occasionally CC with mixed results due to high resists or root immune mobs.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Without a doubt, once I get level 70 and all the new tank AAs I'm going to walk into GoD and steam through a lot of trials, but not without a somewhat bitter taste in my mouth.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Just touching back to what I said earlier, even just giving us increased aggro would improve our survivability and with high skill (ie, casting patch heals inbetween combat rounds) a Paladin could tank rather well.</DIV>
																		
