									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 163 times<br>
									</span>

									
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
DoctorClaw wrote:<BR>
<DIV>Arbosch</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>That warriors will be better at <STRONG>pure </STRONG>tanking than ANY other class (including Knights) should not be questioned. </DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Pure.&nbsp; That's the key word in the sentence, yes?&nbsp; Pure tanking.&nbsp; As in, paladins <STRONG>without </STRONG>spells will not, and should not, match up against the warrior for defensive capabilities in melee combat.&nbsp; After all, if paladins use their spells, it would not be PURE melee, would it? </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Here's the issue I keep trying to tell warriors.... paladins want their spells, disciplines, abilities,&nbsp;AA skills, etc, to make up the difference to come up to equality in terms defensive capabilities in melee combat.&nbsp; We don't want to exceed warriors, just be equal.&nbsp; And I don't mean equal in the "pure melee" sense either.&nbsp; I mean that paladins would be <STRONG>required</STRONG> to use their spells, abilities, AA skills, etc, in order to defeat mobs at the same rate of success as the warriors.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Balance... where things are equal.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Different classes do not need to take the same path, but they do need to achieve the same result, or there is no balance.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Problem:&nbsp; The paladin's spells, disciplines, AA skills, etc, do NOT cover the gap between warriors and paladins in the melee combat area.&nbsp; There are too many limitations and deficiencies still remaining.&nbsp; This isn't to say the class is gimped, just that it's still got some ground to cover.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Additionally, I'm perfectly fine with having some encounters where the warrior class abilities are clearly superior, so long as (and this is the important part)... so long as there are just as many encounters where the paladin abilities are clearly superior.&nbsp; As of this moment in time, 5+ years of this game's lifespan has yielded zero... count with me... Z-E-R-O paladin preferred encounters.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As far as the single group concerns go, arbosch, we have already seen SOEs answer to this one. How long has it been since a warrrior ability has experienced a direct nerf? But we endure this one in the name of balance. Sure, a warrior who is undergeared could potentially take on a trial boss and win under defensive. But the group he is with has got to be above par on every other category to even think this warrior can tank the mobs gettting to the boss.</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>On this we agree.&nbsp; Now put the overgeared paladin in the position of the undergeared warrior.&nbsp; If they achieve the same level of success, then the paladins are NOT properly balanced against the warrior class</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Don't piss on your potential as a player, arbosch. Knights are VERY strong in all areas they are designed to be a part of. </DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>They're not designed to be tops in the melee DPS group (rogue)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>They're not designed to be tops in the healing group (cleric)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>They're not designed to be tops in the tanking group (warrior)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>They're not designed to be tops in the crowd control group (enchanter)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>They're not designed to be tops in the nuking group (wizard)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>They're not designed to be tops in the pet classes (magician / beastlord, take your pick)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>They're not designed to be tops in the dot casting&nbsp; group&nbsp;(shaman / necro, take your pick)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>They're not designed to be tops in the utility group (bard)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>They're not designed to be tops in the soloing group (necro / druid, take your pick)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>They're not designed to be tops in the buffing group (shaman)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>They're not designed to be tops in the pulling group (monk)</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>I'll be the first one to say that paladins can be a great addition to a group.&nbsp; But what are paladins designed for?&nbsp; What makes a group say, "boy we need a&nbsp;knight for THAT job?"</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>A brief stint as the best taunter in the game caused raucous shouts from the warriors.&nbsp; So I too would as, what do warriors feel SHOULD be the knights unquestioned area of expertise?&nbsp; What would YOU designate as the perfect job for the knights (I'm including shadow knights here) to perform such that even a warrior would call in a paladin over a cleric or&nbsp;ranger or&nbsp;beastlord?</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As far as rangers tanking better than knights, even for a 30 second encounter, I doubt this is a major issue once knights finally get an avoidance disc. Knights will always win out over rangers as group tanks due to higher AC and higher HP.</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>And there's the rub.&nbsp; It's not a major issue once we have it, but unfortunately, we don't have it.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What do knights need to be able to tank better?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1) Avoidance discs for those emergency moments</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>What scares me is that some idgit will provide an avoidance disc to the knights and then give it a "beyond stupid" reuse timer&nbsp;of 72 minutes.&nbsp; A warrior can use Defensive every 10 minutes with a 3 minute duration (21 minutes duration across 72 minute period of time), but knights are more likely to be passed off as "just another hybrid" and get 30 seconds worth of duration across a 72 timespan.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>These same idgits will&nbsp;then pronounce everything&nbsp;as being fixed and&nbsp;paladins will&nbsp;get ignored, or called whiners, for not being grateful at&nbsp;being thrown a&nbsp;mere crumb.&nbsp;</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2) Paladins need a way to use stuns even on stun immune mobs, for effect. Limit its abuse somehow, to avoid stun lock.</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>At the current time, the durations on stuns are mitigated.&nbsp; A stun that is supposed to last 10 seconds *never* gets to see the full 10-second duration.&nbsp;&nbsp;100% of mobs mitigate against stuns.&nbsp; Aside from the 9-point AA skill that hits level 68 mobs, stuns are up against the following</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>-Max mob level of 65.&nbsp; 100% resistance against mobs level 66+</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>-Stun immune mobs.&nbsp; There are *many* in the EPs and beyond.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>-Stun mitigation.&nbsp; Stuns *never* go the full duration.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>None of the above is an exaggeration.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>I wonder what warriors would say if there were as many Defensive-immune mobs as there are Stun-immune mobs?</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3) Shadowknights need a way to mitigate or avoid damage comparable to the same level that paladins use stuns. Some neat ideas on this, such as a percentage reverse damage shield or an accuracy debuff.</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Shadow knights *do* have a way to mitigate damage comparable to paladin stuns.&nbsp; And from what I'm told, it meets with about the same level of success.&nbsp; It's called Feign Death.&nbsp; (humor.&nbsp; don't flame).</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Personally, the only thing holding me to this game at this point is the friends I still have left playing. And even they are talking about leaving EQ once WoW or EQ2 goes gold. And a large nunmber of those are already burnt on SOE products (can anyone say SWG?) so I think Blizzard is going to see the influx of a lot of EQ refugees.</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Casual players are not going to see the gear upgrades that raiders do.&nbsp; That's fine.&nbsp; But that means they need something else to hold their attention.&nbsp; And that means "character development" thru AA skills, trade skills, levels, spells, abilities, etc.&nbsp; Upgrade spells and skills are NOT new.&nbsp; They're just different numbers applied to the same abilities.&nbsp; The limited imagination put into the spells and AA skills makes me seriously doubt this game will continue more than another 3-4 expansions, unless new ideas are injected.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
																		
