<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Well on our server, Tholuxe Paels the paladin numbers have dropped steadily for the last 3 months. A good number have re-rolled (beastlords are popular)&nbsp;but quite a few have left. The second biggest guild on our server which was represented by their guild leader at the summit, is&nbsp;gradually becoming a world of warcraft guild. I am a member of the top euro guild on our server and we have lost a good 40% of our players in the last 2 months, 50 people at a raid is a strong showing for us, we normally are running through zones like Uqua with 4-5 clerics. Our server is dying, looks like world of warcraft is drawing a crowd.</P>
<P>&nbsp;If they dont solve the&nbsp;problems who cares? Ultimately it is our choice&nbsp;whether we put up with what the Frodlins of the world say is fair /shrug. Let SoE do whatever it wants, let people like Frodlin be all happy they get to be the only one to tank the mobs, see how cool it is when they are the only ones left to fight the mobs, happy soloing chump. If they dont fix the problems, just leave, I think SoE has had fair warning.</P>
<P>Alvret<BR></P>
