				<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=15619'>			
	
		</a><br>

				<span class=text_smallest>
								</span>

								
			
			
									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 59 times<br>
									</span>

									
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												Lanceor, what can I say? My opinion was asked for. But, as expected, paladins can't let it stand on its own. I can see on a lot of issues we agree.<br><br>1) Yes, warriors should always be better at PURE tanking. That means outside of any disc or any spells. And yes, paladin spells should make up for a large portion of the gap between warrior and knight tanking, and in some ways (as far as aggro) exceed warrior abilities.<br><br>But inside discs or spells, warriors are by far the heaviest tank available in game. And I DO expect to see more defensive "immune" mobs, as what was seen in GoD is most likely the tip of the iceberg.<br><br>No one will ever argue on this one. In situations where extreme survivability is not a factor, a knight brings much more to a group than a warrior ever could. Nuff said on this.<br><br>2) Apparently we agree on this, according to you. But then you throw this whole hypothesis about putting in an overgeared paladin into the mix (?). Check my facts, but aren't overgeared paladins making their ways through GoD Trials with good rates of success now, at least better than undergeared warriors?<br><br>3) Hate to break the news to you. When your class is designed to have a multitude of abilities, you will never be the "best" at any of these single areas. My qualifier was that knights are very strong, not necessarily the "tops". It is the ability to mix the abilities your class has been given that is your strength. Sure, a cleric and a warrior will always be able to outheal/outtank you, but neither one could do it alone, while you, as a paladin is both able to outtank a cleric and outheal a warrior. But there are several jobs where a knight is imminently more desirable than warriors. For instance, any fight where fast aggro makes all the difference between failure and success (GoD Death Traps anyone?).<br><br>4) If your read on, my suggestion is that you SHOULD get it.<br><br>5) Warrior avoidance discs, which last 12 seconds, are on a 36 minute timer. If you want a 24 second avoidance disc (like rangers), then you will have to live with a 72 minute reuse timer, just like rangers do. About the only class that doesn't follow the avoidance disc timer ratio is monks, and that's because of their specialization as pullers.  Defensive is on a 10 minute timer, but this is the warrior ability that defines them as heavy raid tanks.<br><br>6) You know, if I were to be harping on the SOE development team on one issue, as a paladin, THIS would be the one. Stuns are a paladin signature ability. No other class is as dependent upon them, nor does any other class get as many. Stuns are both a source of aggro, as well as a form of damage avoidance. And you wonder why SOE made so many mobs stun immune? And why your stuns are bouncing off mabs due to a level limit? Because, if left unchecked, stuns would be abused. It's happened before, it can happen again. So why not find a way to fix them? Hmmmmm???<br><br>7) Shadowknights (IMHO) are really the only knight class that has ANY room to complain about the hand they've been dealt. They are the offensive oriented knight, yet they can barely outdamage warrriors. They don't have the ability to stun avoid damage like paladins can. In fact, their line of terror spells have never even worked as advertised, so their ability to generate aggro is below that of paladins, and in some situations, worse than warriors. You want to talk about problems tanking in GoD? At least Paladins can rez their party if there is a wipe. What can SKs do? FD?<br><br>8) When the "price" of entry to ANY of the higher content in GoD was the possession of raid level gear, then that means nearly the entire expansion was WORTHLESS to the casual player. Check and see where pickup groups are still forming. 10 to 1 that if you put up LFG, you will get a dozen offers for BoT or LDON for every single offer you get for Elementals or GoD. Trust me, casual players who may have only one or two hours at a time to play will find another game that doesn't require huge time sinks to advance like EQ does.
																		
										</td></tr>
